  "chapter": {
    "number": 43,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Only Savior"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now this is what the LORD says—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He who created you, O Jacob,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and He who formed you, O Israel:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Do not fear, for I have redeemed you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have called you by your name; you are Mine!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When you pass through the waters,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will be with you;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and when you go through the rivers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will not overwhelm you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When you walk through the fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will not be scorched;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the flames will not set you ablaze.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I am the LORD your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel, your Savior;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I give Egypt for your ransom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Cush",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2662
          },
          {
            "text": "and Seba in your place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because you are precious and honored in My sight,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and because I love you,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will give men in exchange for you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and nations in place of your life.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be afraid, for I am with you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will bring your offspring from the east",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and gather you from the west.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will say to the north, ‘Give them up!’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the south, ‘Do not hold them back!’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Bring My sons from afar,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My daughters from the ends of the earth—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "everyone called by My name and created for My glory,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whom I have indeed formed and made.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bring out a people who have eyes but are blind,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and who have ears but are deaf.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the nations gather together",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the peoples assemble.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Who among them can declare this,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and proclaim to us the former things?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let them present their witnesses to vindicate them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that others may hear and say, “It is true.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“You are My witnesses,” declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“and My servant whom I have chosen,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you may consider and believe Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and understand that I am He.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Before Me no god was formed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and after Me none will come.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I, yes I, am the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no Savior but Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I alone decreed and saved and proclaimed—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I, and not some foreign god among you.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So you are My witnesses,” declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“that I am God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even from eternity I am He,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and none can deliver out of My hand.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When I act, who can reverse it?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Way in the Wilderness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD your Redeemer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“For your sake, I will send to Babylon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bring them all as fugitives,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even the Chaldeans,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2663
          },
          {
            "text": "in the ships in which they rejoice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am the LORD, your Holy One,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Creator of Israel, and your King.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD, who makes a way in the sea",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a path through the surging waters,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who brings out the chariots and horses,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the armies and warriors together,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to lie down, never to rise again;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to be extinguished, snuffed out like a wick:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Do not call to mind the former things;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "pay no attention to the things of old.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, I am about to do something new;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "even now it is coming. Do you not see it?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, I will make a way in the wilderness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and streams in the desert.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The beasts of the field will honor Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the jackals",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2664
          },
          {
            "text": "and the ostriches,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2665
          },
          {
            "text": "because I provide water in the wilderness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and rivers in the desert,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to give drink to My chosen people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The people I formed for Myself",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will declare My praise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Unfaithfulness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But you have not called on Me, O Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because you have grown weary of Me, O Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have not brought Me sheep for burnt offerings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor honored Me with your sacrifices.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have not burdened you with offerings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor wearied you with frankincense.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have not bought Me sweet cane with your silver,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor satisfied Me with the fat of your sacrifices.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "But you have burdened Me with your sins;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have wearied Me with your iniquities.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I, yes I, am He",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who blots out your transgressions for My own sake",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and remembers your sins no more.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remind Me, let us argue the matter together.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "State your case, so that you may be vindicated.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your first father sinned,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your spokesmen rebelled against Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So I will disgrace the princes of your sanctuary,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will devote Jacob to destruction",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2666
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel to reproach.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
